her mothering instincts

35:29.228 --> 35:30.494
are superlative.

35:30.496 --> 35:31.528
Her license.

35:31.530 --> 35:32.863
Really on my game today.

35:34.500 --> 35:35.732
And on that page,

35:35.734 --> 35:37.834
9-22-2014,

35:37.836 --> 35:40.303
the day I first met
Walter O'Brien.

35:42.574 --> 35:44.608
That's important because

35:44.610 --> 35:46.743
it's the day I realized
I wasn't alone.

35:46.745 --> 35:49.746
He taught me there
were others like me

35:49.748 --> 35:51.515
who cared about me.

35:51.517 --> 35:53.316
Um...

35:53.318 --> 35:55.385
I can verify
that date with, uh,

35:55.387 --> 35:57.721
an invoice from the owner
of Nemos Diner

35:57.723 --> 36:01.158
where I was fixing a router
and when I first met Ms. Dineen

36:01.160 --> 36:02.893
and her amazing son, Ralph.

36:02.895 --> 36:04.861
I didn't ask.

36:07.299 --> 36:09.466
Okay, it's just, uh...

36:10.903 --> 36:12.736
...it was a very important day
in my life, too.

36:14.573 --> 36:16.907
I'm gonna quit while I'm ahead.

36:16.909 --> 36:19.643
Defense, any cross?

36:19.645 --> 36:22.812
We have nothing
at this time.

36:22.814 --> 36:24.347
Then I have a ruling.

36:24.349 --> 36:27.284
Your client should be
ashamed of himself.

36:27.286 --> 36:29.619
I rule in favor of Plaintiff.

36:29.621 --> 36:30.921
(cheering)

36:30.923 --> 36:32.556
He hit the little hammer
in my favor.

36:33.592 --> 36:34.691
It's the first time ever.

36:34.693 --> 36:35.692
(laughing)

36:35.694 --> 36:36.760
I'm a winner!

36:36.762 --> 36:38.195
Yeah!

36:42.634 --> 36:43.934
I keep thinking
the judge is gonna call

36:43.936 --> 36:45.402
and reverse the decision,

36:45.404 --> 36:46.636
but it's not legal.

36:46.638 --> 36:47.704
I checked.

36:47.706 --> 36:49.839
You did an amazing job.

36:49.841 --> 36:51.575
Oh, thanks.

36:51.577 --> 36:53.677
You have a really fantastic
group of people here.

36:53.679 --> 36:56.580
Supportive... forgiving.

36:56.582 --> 36:59.516
Um, and I just wanted
to thank you for...

36:59.518 --> 37:01.551
for helping me
believe in myself.

37:01.553 --> 37:02.852
You should.

37:02.854 --> 37:05.255
You're... a really good lawyer.

37:05.257 --> 37:06.489
Thank you.

37:06.491 --> 37:08.558
(phone ringing)

37:08.560 --> 37:10.927
Oh, it's my mom.

37:10.929 --> 37:13.563
Yeah, hi, Mom. Yeah, I won.

37:13.565 --> 37:16.566
Uh-huh, yeah,
I can't believe it either.

37:16.568 --> 37:17.734
Hey, buddy.

37:22.441 --> 37:25.442
It means a lot to me

37:25.444 --> 37:28.912
that you put the day that
we first met in your code.

37:28.914 --> 37:32.415
I'm sorry for being curt
with you before.

37:32.417 --> 37:33.483
It's okay.

37:33.485 --> 37:34.584
No, it's not.

37:34.586 --> 37:36.920
I, um...

37:36.922 --> 37:38.421
it won't happen again.

37:39.691 --> 37:41.625
I do, though, believe

37:41.627 --> 37:44.694
in what I said.

37:44.696 --> 37:45.895
Okay?

37:45.897 --> 37:47.998
I couldn't understand

37:48.000 --> 37:50.767
the details
in your incredibly complex code.

37:51.536 --> 37:53.870
I used to think
that I-I had

37:53.872 --> 37:55.672
the fourth highest
IQ in the world,

37:55.674 --> 38:00.677
but now I realized that you have
dropped me down to number five.

38:00.679 --> 38:02.912
That's what got you upset?

38:02.914 --> 38:04.648
(laughing): No.

38:04.650 --> 38:08.785
No, what upset me is that
you were willing to slow down

38:08.787 --> 38:10.687
for me to-to let me
go down the wrong road,

38:10.689 --> 38:12.055
when that would've hindered you,

38:12.057 --> 38:14.958
because I couldn't
grasp your work.

38:14.960 --> 38:18.662
Never hobble your intelligence
for anyone...

38:18.664 --> 38:21.331
because if you do that
in this garage,

38:21.333 --> 38:24.501
imagine what you'll
have to do out there...

38:24.503 --> 38:26.703
for humans.

38:26.705 --> 38:29.873
The world needs
to catch up to you...

38:29.875 --> 38:32.475
because if-if it can,
just a little,

38:32.477 --> 38:34.577
imagine what a...

38:34.579 --> 38:36.680
a beautiful place it could be.

38:36.682 --> 38:38.682
(door opens)

38:38.684 --> 38:40.717
CABE:
Hey, Walter.

38:40.719 --> 38:43.553
You have a visitor.

38:43.555 --> 38:44.587
WALTER:
Oh, hey...

38:44.589 --> 38:45.722
Linda...

38:48.360 --> 38:50.727
Um, thanks for meeting me here.

38:51.830 --> 38:52.896
You... are you ready?

38:52.898 --> 38:54.764
Looks like a fun party.

38:54.766 --> 38:55.665
We can stay.

38:55.667 --> 38:57.534
You can finish
your plate.

38:57.536 --> 38:59.369
Oh, yes, the, uh,
the jalapeno poppers.

38:59.371 --> 39:01.805
They're... actually,
the capsaicin in the jalapeno

39:01.807 --> 39:03.106
has many health benefits.

39:03.108 --> 39:04.941
Cool, I'll give one a shot.

39:04.943 --> 39:06.776
Oh, no, no, no!

39:06.778 --> 39:08.611
There's corn in the batter, yeah.
Oh.

39:08.613 --> 39:10.046
Ooh! (chuckles)

39:10.047 --> 39:11.480
Yeah, uh, I-I remember
on our first date

39:11.483 --> 39:13.100
you said you were allergic, right?
Oh.

39:13.101 --> 39:14.718
(laughs) Yeah, you think
I would know that.

39:14.720 --> 39:16.119
Yeah.

39:16.121 --> 39:18.388
Uh, actually,
I did know that.

39:20.692 --> 39:23.960
But you were gonna
eat it anyway?

39:23.962 --> 39:27.063
Guess you make me adventurous.

39:28.967 --> 39:31.568
Linda, may I ask you a question?

39:31.570 --> 39:32.969
Of course.

39:32.971 --> 39:34.704
Do you really like me?

39:34.706 --> 39:36.806
Or does being around me

39:36.808 --> 39:40.643
remind you of a sense memory
when you were saved,

39:40.645 --> 39:42.712
and that's what you,
uh, really like?

39:42.714 --> 39:45.415
Is... because I-I think
it's the latter.

39:45.417 --> 39:46.716
That's crazy.
Is it?

39:46.718 --> 39:48.017
(chuckles)
Is, um...

39:48.019 --> 39:51.121
do you really like
fermented fish and-and,

39:51.123 --> 39:53.556
uh, smelly flowers?

39:53.558 --> 39:58.561
D-Do you like a guy who likes
those-those kind of things?

40:00.132 --> 40:01.931
Wow.

40:03.702 --> 40:05.735
I'm not sure.

40:05.737 --> 40:07.837
Uh...

40:07.839 --> 40:09.939
it would explain how

40:09.941 --> 40:14.043
I sat through that documentary
on African bee migration.

40:16.548 --> 40:19.616
Well, that's, uh, it's-it's okay
that you don't really like me.

40:21.052 --> 40:22.152
(sighs)

40:22.154 --> 40:23.853
But...

40:23.855 --> 40:25.855
what you're doing for me

40:25.857 --> 40:27.891
right now makes me...

40:27.893 --> 40:29.793
like you.

40:30.829 --> 40:33.863
Just not in-in that kind of way.

40:33.865 --> 40:36.766
(sighs)

40:36.768 --> 40:38.835
It's okay, it's okay.

40:38.837 --> 40:40.904
I understand.

40:42.574 --> 40:44.541
Uh...

40:44.543 --> 40:45.909
still friends?

40:45.911 --> 40:47.710
(laughs)

40:47.712 --> 40:49.813
Always friends.

40:53.685 --> 40:56.186
Oh, yeah.

40:58.957 --> 40:59.956
(sighs)

40:59.958 --> 41:02.759
Um...

41:02.761 --> 41:05.462
good-bye, smarty-pants.

41:05.464 --> 41:06.529
(chuckles)

41:08.900 --> 41:10.700
(sighs)

41:10.702 --> 41:11.734
Hey.
Hi.

41:11.736 --> 41:13.503
I just wanted to say bye.

41:13.505 --> 41:15.672
I'm getting on a plane
going to Seattle,

41:15.674 --> 41:17.640
uh, see a specialist
about my back,

41:17.642 --> 41:18.875
hopefully get cleared for duty.

41:18.877 --> 41:19.876
Oh.

41:19.878 --> 41:21.478
I hope that works out for you.

41:21.480 --> 41:22.846
Me, too. Um,

41:22.848 --> 41:26.783
regardless, I was thinking
when I got back,

41:26.785 --> 41:30.887
maybe you and I could
get a meal together...

41:30.889 --> 41:32.255
at a restaurant--

41:32.257 --> 41:34.157
a real restaurant,
not Kovelsky's.

41:34.159 --> 41:35.258
(chuckles)

41:35.260 --> 41:37.227
Oh, like a...

41:37.229 --> 41:39.562
date?
Date, yes.

41:39.564 --> 41:41.498
Only if you'd like.

41:44.769 --> 41:46.736
Yeah, I would love to.

41:46.738 --> 41:48.671
Great.

41:48.673 --> 41:50.415
Would you look at them?
He's dealing with her,

41:50.416 --> 41:52.158
she's dealing with him,
and they should be

41:52.159 --> 41:53.901
dealing with each other.
They're morons.

41:53.902 --> 41:55.644
That's never gonna be us--
we keep it easy, right?

41:56.748 --> 41:58.281
Whoa.
Oh, oh...

41:58.283 --> 42:01.084
King Klutz over here, I'm sorry.

42:02.587 --> 42:04.687
Okay, Doc, I'll live.

42:05.657 --> 42:08.057
I'm grab us some, uh,
guac and chips.

42:11.796 --> 42:14.197
Make sure you
get it right.

42:14.199 --> 42:16.666
With this stain,
I can extrapolate

42:16.668 --> 42:20.003
her ring size
in five minutes.

42:21.907 --> 42:23.907
Just keeping it easy.
